dspace-development.title: Troubleshoot and document the solution for authentication issues on the Symplectic Elements QA and Production environments

comments.body:
At this point, there are transport-layer issues affecting the ability for clients on the Elements servers to be able to communicate with PULibrary web servers. I have been evaluating and testing the various instructions specified on https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/framework/network-programming/tls, along with using https://gist.github.com/jrgriffiniii/3bb229955645f17a36bc3e0560add9b5 in an attempt to diagnose these connectivity problems.

I am now attempting to restart the `dev` server in order to use updated Windows registry values. Should this prove to be ineffective, I will need to resort to exclusively relying upon OIT for support and assistance.
https://princeton.service-now.com/service?id=ticket&table=incident&sys_id=09ed2bbf1b6fd010435885d56b4bcbec&view=sp was created after another attempt at resolving these issues myself.
